 Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of   Maria   and   Margit  , now also used as an independent given name and as an element of compound names such as <i>Mai-Britt</i>, <i>Mai-Lis</i>, <i>Anne-Mai</i>, and <i>Britt-Mai</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Murchadha","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Modern Gaelic form of the traditional name <i>Muireadhach</i>;  see  Murdo ."],"variants":[{"name":"Murrough","meanings":["Modern Gaelic form of the traditional name <i>Muireadhach</i>;  see  Murdo ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Art Mór Mac Murchadha Caomhánachh King of Leinster was born about 1305, in Diocese of Dublin, Ireland, his father, Murrough Roe Caomhánach, was 41 and his mother, Mrs Muirceartach Kavanagh, was 37. He married Mrs Art Mor Kavanagh Art Mor Mac Murchadha Caomhanachh about 1348, in Ireland. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died in 1377, at the age of 73, and was buried in St Mullin's, County Carlow, Ireland."},"et":{"Abt 1305–1377":"umbes 1305–1377","1295–1350":"1295–1350","1305–1377":"1305–1377","1305–Female":"1305–Surnud","1350–1361":"1350–1361","1356–1402":"1356–1402","1357–1417":"1357–1417","1265–1354":"1265–1354","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","from 1354 to 1362":"1354 kuni 1362","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","1295":"1295","1270":"1270","Abt 1305":"umbes 1305","1305":"1305","1402":"1402","1357":"1357","1356":"1356","1377":"1377","1354":"1354","about 1348":"umbes 1348","1375":"1375","about 1304":"umbes 1304","1265":"1265","from 1369 to 1375":"1369 kuni 1375","1417":"1417","Diocese of Dublin, Leinster, Ireland":"Diocese of Dublin, Iirimaa","Ireland":"Iirimaa","St Mullin's, County Carlow, Ireland":"St Mullin's, County Carlow, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"Abt 1305–1377":"noin 1305–1377","1295–1350":"1295–1350","1305–1377":"1305–1377","1305–Female":"1305–Kuollut","1350–1361":"1350–1361","1356–1402":"1356–1402","1357–1417":"1357–1417","1265–1354":"